maybelater: <p>
@nicocasel, A <code>db_version()</code> method wasn't implemented as it wasn't required.
</p>
<p>
If you require that function you can use the code as shown here:
<a class="ext-link" href="https://make.wordpress.org/core/2014/04/07/mysql-in-wordpress-3-9/#comment-13174"><span class="icon">​</span>https://make.wordpress.org/core/2014/04/07/mysql-in-wordpress-3-9/#comment-13174</a>
</p>
<pre class="wiki">if ( empty( $wpdb-&gt;use_mysqli ) ) {
    $ver = mysql_get_server_info();
} else {
    $ver = mysqli_get_server_info( $wpdb-&gt;dbh );
}
</pre>
